Hi @Stephen-Hazel!

You have a few options:

* Use the [`editable_complete`](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-editable.html#editable-edit-complete) triggered event (default is `editComplete`) to modify the cell contents after pasting... but it's probably not the most efficient method. Since you would need to update the cache a second time.
* Use the [`editable_validate`](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-editable.html#editable-validate) callback function and have it return the modified text:

    ```js
    $('table').tablesorter({
      widgets : ['editable'],
      widgetOptions : {
        // global validate function
        editable_validate : function(txt, orig, columnIndex, $element){
          return $element.text();
        }
      }
    });
    ```

* Lastly, you could use the right click "Paste as plain text" method

    ![test](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/136959/9284191/3ea071fa-429f-11e5-9b1e-1cf0e373c9ea.gif)

Or, maybe you were asking me to add something internally to prevent pasting in HTML? That shouldn't be a problem, but I would likely add an option to use or not use that functionality.

Hi @AntonyThason!

As stated before, the pager only works with the first non-info tbody.

@karthickkumarganesh, I don't know why I didn't think of this before, but you could use the [`ajaxProcessing` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#object) to add the data to the separate tbodies, something like this:

```js
ajaxProcessing: function(result, table, xhr){
    if (result && 'data' in result) {
        var c = table.config,
            data = {};
        // "total" is a required property!
        data.total = result["total_rows"];

        c.$tbodies.eq(0).html( result.tbody1 );
        c.$tbodies.eq(1).html( result.tbody2 );

        return data;
    }
}
```

The `totalRows` value will not be accurate, because the pager will only page through that many rows, so maybe you can modify the `output` option to not include it.

Also, the `fixedHeight` will only work on the first tbody.

Other than that, I think it will work, but I haven't tested it.

