I think I'd first need to know the exact semantics you want before I can try to suggest how to implement this. For example, if we have:

	class A(object):
		pass

	@foo
	@ray.remote
	@bar
	class B(A):
		def __init__(self):
			super(B, self).__init__()

	C = B
	B = A

	C.remote()

What behavior do you want? Do you have any preference for any behavior? Or is it perhaps entirely undefined?

Also note that the first usage is wrong for any class except the most-derived class in the hierarchy. (i.e. if someone inherited from `B` then this would break.)

@Vangelis66 `SAMPLE-AES` is different encryption scheme where NAL units are optionally encrypted with extra information embedded in to the transport streams, rather than encrypted the entire transport stream (as in the regular AES-128 method). This means that you have to parse the transport stream to work out what to decrypt, which is not trivial. [hlsdl](https://github.com/selsta/hlsdl) uses `libav` to support MPEG-TS, which is probably why it's written in C :) 
`SAMPLE-AES` support isn't impossible, but it's unlikely as it doesn't seem to appear in the wild much unless when used with DRM - probably because platforms such as Wowza and Unified Streaming use it by default, and you only pay for the licence for those if you wanna use DRM :)

